From: Mixed_ngspice
Subject: Add Cmin stepping and per-node Solution Limiting to DC solver

Two solver-side convergence enhancements with zero double overhead:

Part A — Solution Limiting (sollim):
  Adds per-node delta-V clamping after each Newton solve step,
  preventing the first iteration from overshooting into FP32
  subthreshold NaN regions. Reuses existing CKTabsDv/CKTrelDv
  fields. Enable with: .option sollim

Part B — Cmin stepping:
  Adds a new fallback stage between gmin and source stepping.
  Steps a large diagonal conductance (1e-2) down to zero over
  N iterations, providing numerical damping without altering
  the final DC solution (unlike gmin). Enable with:
    .option cminsteps=10

Files modified:
  src/include/ngspice/cktdefs.h     — CKTuseSolLim, CKTcmin, CKTnumCminSteps, CKTcminFactor
  src/include/ngspice/tskdefs.h     — corresponding TSK fields
  src/include/ngspice/optdefs.h     — OPT_SOLLIM, OPT_CMIN, OPT_CMINSTEPS, OPT_CMINFACTOR
  src/spicelib/analysis/cktsopt.c   — option handlers + table entries
  src/spicelib/analysis/cktntask.c  — defaults + def→tsk copy
  src/spicelib/analysis/cktdojob.c  — tsk→ckt copy
  src/maths/ni/niiter.c            — per-node solution limiting logic
  src/spicelib/analysis/cktop.c     — Cmin stepping function

Verified: 8/8 PTM 45nm open tests pass (DC+AC+TRAN), no regression.
